Mr. Hu is a client manager at the company with over three years of work experience. He is meticulous and diligent in his work and is expected to be promoted within the year.

Recently, he noticed that Mr. Wong's account suddenly engaged in large transactions involving various financial products, including stocks, bonds, funds, and stock options, which is significantly different from his past behavior. Based on Mr. Hu's knowledge, Mr. Wong's salary income has not increased substantially.

He suspects that Mr. Wong may be involved in money laundering.

What measures can Mr. Hu take?

I. Immediately freeze Mr. Wong's account to prevent further transactions that could lead to more serious criminal activities;

II. Disclose the information to the Joint Financial Intelligence Unit and promptly notify Mr. Wong that he is suspected of money laundering, requesting an explanation of the situation;

III. Report the situation to the Money Laundering Reporting Officer and senior management. If no immediate action is required, the account's transactions may continue;

IV. Conduct appropriate inquiries with Mr. Wong and review all available information related to him

